{
  "texts": [
    "In the limit D ds → D s, which is to say sources at infinity, cT ds → D d.",
    "Thus cT ds is a replacement for distance D which we used in Sect. 1.3 when introducing the general picture.",
    "The quantity cr is known as the critical density for strong lensing, because it turns out to be the threshold for appearance of multiple images.",
    "(It is not the cosmological critical density, which has different dimensions.)",
    "For typical lens and source redshifts cr comes to a few kg m -2 -about the surface density of window glass (see Appendix B)."
  ]
}